{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-blog-post-js","path":"/blog/2014/07/octotree/","result":{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"Kevin McKelvin"}},"markdownRemark":{"id":"3c3bc063-4a4b-5c88-8fd2-cc5859fc5978","excerpt":"I was introduced to a Chrome extension yesterday by Kenneth Kalmer that’s completely changed my Github experience. Introducing Octotree, a sidebar for Github…","html":"<p>I was introduced to a Chrome extension yesterday by Kenneth Kalmer that’s completely changed my Github experience. Introducing Octotree, a sidebar for Github that shows a repository’s code in a tree structure.</p>\n<p>Take a look-see</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 590px;\"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/054218b0aa74ae4b10ed2860a9b40a24/b6d14/octotree.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 58.617747440273035%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"Octotree\"\n        title=\"Octotree\"\n        src=\"/static/054218b0aa74ae4b10ed2860a9b40a24/88218/octotree.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/054218b0aa74ae4b10ed2860a9b40a24/7237a/octotree.jpg 148w,\n/static/054218b0aa74ae4b10ed2860a9b40a24/0cfdf/octotree.jpg 295w,\n/static/054218b0aa74ae4b10ed2860a9b40a24/88218/octotree.jpg 590w,\n/static/054218b0aa74ae4b10ed2860a9b40a24/77d57/octotree.jpg 885w,\n/static/054218b0aa74ae4b10ed2860a9b40a24/b6d14/octotree.jpg 1172w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>I’d call that pretty rad!</p>\n<p>You can download the extension by going to <a href=\"https://chrome.google.com/webstore/detail/octotree/bkhaagjahfmjljalopjnoealnfndnagc\">Octotree on the Chrome Web Store</a></p>\n<p>After that, just browse to a Github repository and hit Ctrl+Shift+S or Cmd+Shift+S and you’re set! To browse private repositories you’ll have to set up an API token. Instructions will show up in the sidebar when you’re browsing a private repo.</p>\n<p>(Edited on 2018-03-31 to update the keyboard shortcuts)</p>","frontmatter":{"title":"Octotree","date":"July 03, 2014","description":null}}},"pageContext":{"isCreatedByStatefulCreatePages":false,"slug":"/2014-07-03-octotree/","previous":{"fields":{"slug":"/2014-06-19-renaming-items-in-a-ruby-hash/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"Renaming Items in a Ruby Hash","date":"2014-06-19T00:00:00.000Z","slug":null}},"next":{"fields":{"slug":"/2014-07-07-recurring-tasks-with-sidetiq/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"Recurring Tasks With Sidetiq","date":"2014-07-07T00:00:00.000Z","slug":null}}}}}